If there are stones left (s > 0), set a[i][j] to '*', then decrement s. Otherwise, set it to '.'. Ah right, that makes sense. So the missing code in the TODO part should be: set a[i][j] to '*', then decrease s by 1. So the code would be:

a[i][j] = '*';
s--;

Because in each iteration, when s is positive, we place a stone and reduce the count.
